# Internal tools access gate (/internal/*) — real per-user accounts via Supabase Auth.
# Sign-up (/internal/signup) is restricted server-side (and again by a Postgres trigger,
# see the supabase_auth_internal migration) to @byteflowsolutions.com emails. Sign-in/up/
# out call Supabase Auth directly (supabase-js signInWithPassword/signUp/signOut) — no
# app-managed session secret or shared password anymore.
#
# Supabase project backing the internal tools (Auth + CRM + budgets) — see
# SUPABASE-SETUP.md. Server-only: read exclusively by middleware/API routes/Server
# Components; the browser never talks to Supabase directly and no NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_*
# variable may ever exist here.
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# Existing site vars (already configured in deployment; listed here for completeness):
# CONTENTFUL_SPACE_ID=
# CONTENTFUL_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# CONTENTFUL_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=  (only for npm run generate:types)
# SENDGRID_API_KEY=                  (contact form)
# SENDGRID_FROM_EMAIL=
# SENDGRID_TEMPLATE_ID=
# GOOGLE_SHEET_WEBHOOK_URL=
